Trzy Lipy  is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Kętrzyn, within Kętrzyn County, Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship, in northern Poland. It lies approximately  south-west of Kętrzyn and  north-east of the regional capital Olsztyn.
